    "contenu": "The document contains recipes for two cocktails, named \"Myra Breckinridge\" and \"Park Life Swizzle.\" Below is the structured content of the cocktail recipes:\n\n---\n\n### Myra Breckinridge\n**Creator:** Phil Ward, 2008  \n**Source:** Anthony Sarnicola, a regular at the bar  \n**Description:** Named this drink and described it as \"a sex change for Laphroaig.\"\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 2 ounces Laphroaig 10-year Scotch\n- 2 dashes Vieux Pontarlier Absinthe\n- ¾ ounce Lime Juice\n- ¼ ounce Cane Sugar Syrup\n\n**Garnish:**\n- 1 Mint Sprig\n\n**Instructions:**\nDry shake all the ingredients, then dump into a pilsner glass filled with crushed ice. Swizzle until cold. Garnish with the mint sprig and serve with a straw.\n\n---\n\n### Park Life Swizzle\n**Creator:** Thomas Waugh, 2009\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 1 ounce Ransom Old Tom Gin\n- 1 ounce Lustau Amontillado Sherry\n- ¼ ounce Velvet Falernum\n- ¼ ounce Lime Juice\n- ¼ ounce Ginger Syrup\n- 6 dashes Angostura Bitters\n\n**Garnish:**\n- 1 Mint Sprig\n\n**Instructions:**\nDry shake all the ingredients (except the bitters), then dump into a pilsner glass filled with crushed ice. Top with the bitters. Garnish with the mint sprig, and serve with a straw."
