    "contenu": "### How to Find Delicious Combinations by \"Matching\" Colors\n\n#### Fred Dexheimer\n*Master Sommelier*\n\n---\n\n**The Underlying Principles**\nSuccessful wine and food pairing rely on simple principles, such as color coordination. Just as we choose clothing colors, the same can apply to wine selection.\n\n**Color and Taste Connection**\n- Similar colors can influence our choices both in fashion and food.\n- It may seem peculiar, but the colors in food and wine can correlate, enhancing how we perceive their flavors.\n\n**Examples of Color Matching**\n- **Greens:** Broccoli and similar vegetables pair well with wines that have vegetal notes.\n- **Reds:** Certain red wines are better suited to dishes with dark sauces or caramelized flavors.\n\n**Implementation in Restaurant Setting**\nDiners often unaware, trust sommeliers to make these matches, which can enhance the dining experience. This can involve pairing wines based on the dominant colors in the dish, like:\n  - Light dishes with white wines.\n  - Robust, red-sauced dishes with deeper red wines.\n\n**Fred's Background**\nFred Dexheimer, an award-winning master sommelier, is the national wine and beverage director for BLT Restaurant Group. He mentors a talented team of sommeliers within Laurent Tourondel's growing restaurant family. Dedicated to wine education and a passionate community supporter, he inspires through various initiatives and participates in New York City charity races."
