    "source": "dokumen.pub_perfect-pairings-a-master-sommeliers-practical-advice-for-partnering-wine-with-food-9780520931664.pdf_page_211",
    "contenu": "### Osso Buco with Mushrooms and Tomatoes\n\n**Serves**: 4\n\n**Ingredients**:\n- 3 tablespoons olive oil\n- 4 veal shanks, 1 to 1½ pounds each\n- 6 tablespoons unsalted butter\n- 2 onions, diced\n- 1½ cups hot beef broth\n- 1 cup dry Marsala or dry red wine\n- 6 tablespoons tomato paste\n- 1 ounce dry porcini, soaked in hot water to cover for 30 minutes\n- 1 pound cremini mushrooms, stemmed and sliced or quartered\n- Salt and freshly ground black pepper\n\n**Instructions**:\n\n1. **Preparation of Veal**:\n   - In a heavy skillet, heat the olive oil over medium-high heat.\n   - Add the veal shanks and cook, turning frequently until well browned on all sides, about 6 to 8 minutes.\n   - Using a slotted spoon, transfer the shanks to a Dutch oven.\n\n2. **Prepare Onion and Mushroom Mix**:\n   - In the same skillet, melt 3 tablespoons of butter over medium heat.\n   - Add the diced onions and sauté until they are translucent, about 8 minutes.\n   - Add the onions to the veal shanks.\n   - In a large bowl, whisk the broth, Marsala, and tomato paste together.\n   - Pour the mixture over the veal and onions in the Dutch oven.\n   - Bring to a gentle boil, then reduce heat to low and cover.\n   - Braise the veal shanks for 1 hour.\n\n3. **Prepare and Add Porcini Mushrooms**:\n   - Strain the porcini mushrooms through a cheesecloth-lined strainer over a bowl, reserving the soaking liquid.\n   - Chop the porcini finely.\n   - Melt the remaining 3 tablespoons butter in a large sauté pan over high heat.\n   - Add the sliced or quartered cremini mushrooms and sauté until the juices are released, about 5 minutes.\n   - Stir the chopped porcini and the reserved soaking liquid into the sautéed cremini mushrooms.\n   - After the veal has cooked for 1 hour, add this mushroom mixture to the Dutch oven.\n   - Continue braising until the veal is tender, 30 minutes to 1 hour longer, depending on the size of the shanks.\n   - Season to taste with salt and pepper.\n\n4. **Service**:\n   - Serve the osso buco directly from the Dutch oven.\n\n**Variation**:\n- You can also braise the veal shanks in a 350-degree oven.\n\n### Notes:\n- The recipe is designed to be paired with blended Sangioveses (Super Tuscan-style)."
  },
